# Developer Rules

***src\content\documentation***

1. Framework Structure
- Use React as the main framework
- Follow component-based architecture
- Keep pages in src/pages directory
- Store components in src/components
- Place layouts in src/layouts
- Maintain utilities in src/utils

2. Code Style
- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Follow ESLint configuration
- Maintain consistent naming conventions
- Use camelCase for variables and functions
- Use PascalCase for components
- Add JSDoc comments for complex functions

3. Component Guidelines
- Create reusable components
- Keep components small and focused
- Use props for component configuration
- Implement proper prop validation
- Avoid prop drilling when possible
- Use composition over inheritance

4. Performance
- Optimize images using react's image components
- Implement lazy loading where appropriate
- Minimize client-side JavaScript
- Use static rendering when possible
- Implement proper caching strategies

5. Version Control
- Follow conventional commits
- Create feature branches from main
- Submit detailed pull requests
- Keep commits atomic and focused
- Write meaningful commit messages

6. Testing
- Write unit tests for utilities
- Create component tests
- Implement end-to-end tests
- Maintain good test coverage
- Follow test-driven development when possible

7. Documentation
- Document component APIs
- Maintain README files
- Add inline documentation for complex logic
- Keep documentation up-to-date
- Document build and deployment processes
